  ["The Relics of Wakening9"] = {
    "483194npcAthridas Bearmantle2078npcAthridas Bearmantle2078775Darnassus2501475247634834486",
    "4831212170121212006/12/09 11:43:40grimnardLoc on this is 43, 59.",
    "4831128622401128622007/06/29 12:21:10CharlzO--The first two relics are found when you walk in. Follow the little tunnel till you come to an opening with two bridges infront of you. At the end of both bridges are little caves with the chests that hold the relics. Careful: There are usually two guys within the caves and there's one (that's possibly on both) that patrols the bridge to your left. \
\
--After that, keep following the tunnel. There will be a place to go infront of you, and tunnel leading off to the right that looks like it \"spiral's\" down. Follow the spiral tunnel. You will eventually come to another bridge that you may cross. There is no relic inside this cave, but a quest. Its up to you if you want to get it. The guy's name is Rageclaw, if I recall correctly... \
**If you do go straight ahead, this will take you to a platform. \
\
--Now, on that plat form, there's usually a guy standing in the middle, and one that patrols the bridge leading to the platform and another patrolling the little bridge that leads you down, along with another that walks on the other bridge straight ahead (or almost) of you. That's where you want to go. It's like a cave - when you first walk in there's approx. 2 guys in that little 'bubble'. There's a tunnel to your right which you want to take. That takes you to another 'bubble' in which there's approx. 2 more guys. Once you kill them, turn to the right and there's your chest with one of the relics sitting out on a 'deck' (looks like one, as it has a railing...). \
**If you didn't go straight ahead, don't worry. \
\
--If you get the quest, that's alright. Now, there's going to be another opening straight ahead, and once more, another that spirals down. Take the spiral first - There's another relic down there. This one is by that beloved Greenpaw dude...whatever his name is...Anyways, there's him (usually lvl 10ish or so) along with a lvl 8, 7, or 9. Once you're done there, move back up the spiral and take the opening on your right. Follow that. You'll come to a little arena-like area. There'll be a large pillar of stone in the middle, with guys walking around it. There IS a little cave bubble down there, but it HAS NO RELIC. This is where rageclaw's body lurks, so he might attack you. He patrols around the pillar. Now, there should be a little pathway to your left, taking you up to the platform. Kill the guys there. (I've describe approx. how many guys are there in the lil dot thing above this one.) You're going to want to take the bridge to your right, leading you into The cave bubble. Kill the guys there and take the one to your left to the next bubble, kill those guys. To your right is the 'deck' with your relic\
\
(Taken from another site)",
    "48316094211361412007/09/30 15:31:29KevinHawkinsIt certainly is hard, but it's doable even at lower levels. If my memory does not deceive me, I did it as lvl 9 hunter and lvl 10 druid.\
\
