    "17388791308792006/09/22 11:05:58hampst0rRun up to the tree in Ashenvale (clear it first :) at 31,32.. Just right click it and you get the quest item.",
    "17385217790521772007/03/16 14:27:56dodobirdTake this back to SW..NOT barrens...yea I should probably read the log.",
    "1738209519102095192007/12/29 19:42:26ZugrimDON'T do it like me. It got me killed 5 times out of pure stupidity and tiredness.\
\
Started in Darkshire and ran to rebel camp in STV to cap the FP. Started running towards BB to cap the FP and sail from there, but failed misserably. Got killed by the tiger that always hides behind the first bush when you enter the \"actual\" STV, and got ganked by a lvl ?? the sec I ress. (was lvl 20 at the time) \"Uh!!! I can do a ghost run all teh way to BB, and even get there faster then\" i thought to myself. And i did it. Got to BB 50% faster, and clicked the spirit healer, and got portet back to the northern STV with ress sickness and an angry tiger next to me.\
\
Then my brain kicked in and i remembered that i could SWIM all the way down there, so I flew to westfall, ran to the coast and swam all the way without even a small NPC in the way. Capped the FP and took the boat.\
\
I arrived happily in Ratchet and capped the FP just to be sure. Moved along the road with auto-walk, and turned my brain off because, \"What could happen to me? It's just The Barrens!\" 2 seconds later I got ganked by a lvl 16 rogue as I was drinking my coffee. After a really long detour around any horde player I could see, I finally got to the blind dude, and did the quest.\
\
Apparentley I threw my brain out teh window as I completed teh quest, because I thought it would be easier to take a shortcut through XR. Boy was i wrong. After some painfull ressing atempts I got on the way to Astralala (or what ever it's called) and capped teh FP there. Stupid as I was I started to fight my way through all the furbolgs instead of following the road because i thought it was a shortcut. Wrong again.\
\
I got to the Heartswood quite painless (Zero kills) after that, and moved along towards Auberdine then. Didn't notice I ran into a Raid on Auberdine untill i read \"You are dead, 6 minutes untill release\" DO'H!!!\
\
Ressed, Sailed to Menethil, flew to SW, completed the quest, Took teh follow-up, killed the succubus, dinged 21, got the summoning spell and (I still regret this part) then banged my head on the desk.\
\
This \"easy\" little quest took me 2h45m to somplete, so if you do it this way, it's your fault.",
    "17386363820636382007/04/08 04:46:30crimsonhellgrWell it is more easy if you go from theramore isle take the east shore and go north to Durotan-barrens. From there go to the npc. \
As you have go theramore means that you was already in Menethil. so before go theramore go Darkshore and take the flight path. go back menethil and take the ship for theramore. Put you heartstone at Theramore Inn and go barrens take the q from the npc that tolds you to go at the tree. click HS and go theramore take flight path to Darkshore do the q and take the ship to menethil. from there flight for SW",
    "17387167611434892007/04/23 15:24:14HeartsOfWarAgreed... if you hug the wall, you shouldn't have any problems; although, I did have to fight two or three mobs. I'm not sure if this was for my own personal taste of not being crowded, but they were a little too close for my comfort, but very solo able around 20 - 21.",
    "173823382023382006/10/28 04:19:28luciphercolorsAlso note that the heartswood tree is protected by a large group of 18-20 Dark Strand warlocks/mages/rogues(?). Heavily guarded.",
    "17384348970434892007/02/27 16:14:52mech6982This is suprisingly easy to get for how 'heavily' defended it is.  I went in at level 22, stayed close to the wall approaching from Astranaar and only had to kill a single mob, sneaking by everything else without aggro'ing.  The Heartswood has a large radius that you can use it from.  Stick close to the wall and use it as soon as you're within range.",
    "1738103146201031462007/06/12 14:31:45JyotaiIf you come at the tree from the southwest (out of Maestra's Post) along the edge of the mountain / trees and keep trying to climb up that mountain and trees as you come along the edge there you can get up behind the root without ever once getting any aggro - get the Heartswood, and leave (either the same path, or hearthstone back to Stormwind and turn it all in).",
    "173813224421636442007/08/04 16:30:15Frag971You can just go around thru the broken wall near haha",
    "1738103291111031462007/06/12 20:38:41JyotaiMy overall path for this began with setting my hearthstone to Stormwind.\
\
I then flew to Menethil harbor from Ironforge, took the boat, and came down from Darkshore into Ashenvale. Got the flight path in Astranaar, then went south through the talondeep pass into Stonetalon and got the flight path there (while I was in the area).\
\
I then went east into the Barrens, taking the northern way around the guard post and then going along the road - avoiding Crossroads to go down to near Camp Turajo and get this part of the quest.\
\
From there I went up to Ratchet, got the flight path, got on the boat to Booty Bay and go the Flight Path to that (at level 20 - you have no chance of walking through STV, so this is a great chance to get that flight path early). Taking the boat back I flew from Ratchet to Astranaar and then walked up to the treem hugging the 'wall' so that I never got any aggro.\
\
Get the Heartswood and hearth back to Stormwind.\
\
A bit extra, but I got several flight paths as a result and it was very easy, albeit time consuming.",
