    "9476531131344182007/04/11 02:30:05IcemeltJust FYI: Spawn times are now based on how fast you kill consecutive mobs. I don't know the \"magic\" on this system, but it seems that (upon late experimentation) if you take your time killing mobs and eat/bandage between kills, the mobs spawn slightly slower.\
\
Also, non-looting still works, but spawn times are not 2x as long like before patch 2.x\
\
(note: non-looting = not touching the loot 'sparkles' until you have cleared an area causing the spawn system to slow down to allow you time to loot)",
    "947182441301824412007/11/11 14:23:14NivraxHunters are somewhat different, at lvl10 they got pet (which on that low level is much tougher even than a Warlocks WV) and with Mend Pet they are able to solo easily most of the quests, even harder ones (one man army - a tank pet, Mend Pet healer and a dpser which ranged skills).\
\
The mobs inside cave ARE hard. Either warriors, which are doing quite a bit damage and cast some sort of spell that knocks you back, interrupting action and, if you are really unlucky, dropping you down to 100% death. Priestes on the other hand casts Smite dealing about 40 holy dmg and when low on hp, heal (that is giving them 100% health back). Add to that big density of mobs there and that Nagas will try to flee, bringing more and more adds (and don`t forget about one or two patrols) and you will get one small hell.\
\
I done this quest 3 times and each time I was able to solo it by going right way (tho at the end I always ended up fighting 2 mobs). However, today (when I was doing this as a 15lvl druid) there was no Death Cap on right side (I figured it out after 20minutes of fight and 2 deaths...). 1 hour later I returned there with a 3 man party and somehow we menaged to get to the Mushrooms (3 of them) located below. However, that way is close to imposible (if not impossible for most classes) to solo due to numerours Nagas and the Twilight Thugs.\
\
In short words - you can try to solo it going the right way BUT if there are no Mushroom, either get a party, a hight level (20 or so) or forget about it.",
    "94714491231344182007/08/27 14:22:26drakaWhen I soloed this cave as a 16 druid, I was the only one in the entire area, so the mob respawn rate was reasonable (because killing things in bear form takes time). \
\
So long as there isn't competition, just go to the right \"upper\" deck like others suggested and by the time you singly defeat the naga and get a death cap (there are actually three), a couple other stalks back at the entrance will have respawned. Don't bother with going into the rest of the cave.\
\
I recommend backing into a wall when facing the melee wave riders since they'll kick you a fair distance.  Watch for patrols, of course, and be sure to kill them quickly at the end since they'll run away and look for friends. This is annoying in caves.",
    "9476534740653472007/04/11 05:23:47IcemeltThis quest is not hard, but can be if you get careless. Your best course of action, due to the faster spawn times, is to take your time and have your Hearthstone ready when you complete. Otherwise you'll be killing your way out.\
\
If you're lucky, you'll get the Death Cap on the upper floor as apposed to inside the cavern deeps.\
\
Warning!: Unless you are sure of yourself and your skill/level, do not attempt to kill the Twilight Thugs. The drop rate for the quest giving book is extremely low. \"IF\" you decide to take them on, your best bet is to use some immoblizing effect on one of the Twilight Thugs and Nuke the caster/healer. You may die at this point. Run back as quickly as possible, immobilize the lower of the two Twilight Thugs and Nuke the other. You 'MAY' die again (this is why it's not worth it to me). Run back quickly, kill the last, hope the healer doesen't respawn, because you 'MAY' die again! If the Twilight Thugs are orange to you, don't even try. I suggest not trying unless at least one of them (probably the healer) is green. (This is based on a Rogue's perspective and may change with other classes.)",
    "947130765301307652007/08/02 00:21:06BrighidHerbalists can use the \"Find Herbs\" ability to track both mushrooms needed on the minimap.  Zoom in and mouseover, it makes it a bit easier.",
    "947525117052512006/11/30 17:09:15Calista1045If your soloing this quest it's easier to go to the right after you enter the cave. There are two death caps up there and only a couple of naga. If your careful they are easily single pulled. The other mushrooms respawn fast so you won't have to go very far into the cave.",
    "9471651953134432007/10/09 13:22:49xinaxdazexThe naga will flee when their health is low and wandering pathers will make their way to you while fighting other mobs, so be careful on this one :)\
\
Calista is right, however. Go to the right when you enter the cave and there's a much easier to get Death Cap then down below.",
    "947183156211626062007/11/13 00:17:59VeraldisThe death caps still spawn in the upper right-hand of the cave, but they seemed to have changed how the respawn frequency works. I was in the cave yesterday on my rogue alt and they were at the \"normal\" spot; when I went back today to help a friend with the quest, there were none. We had to go down the ramp and into the room to the left to find any.\
\
Either get a friend to help you, or come back later and see if they've respawned, I'd say.",
    "947344324034432006/11/11 10:48:04madroxeAt the very east side of the Cliffspring River (55,34), is a cave occupied by Naga.  The Saber Stalk and Death Cap can be found inside.  Be warned though: This area is very dangerous! Even at level 16-17 you can find yourself in serious trouble if you aren't careful...",
