    "1739136139101361392007/08/11 21:46:19abhilashaTo get to the summoning circle...take the staircase behind the trainer. go down the spiral staircase at the end you can go right or left...go left. At the bottom of that go left. Immediately to your left is a staircase, it'll take you straight to the summoning circle. coor of last staircase is 26,79. Hope this helps you all find it as i do circles finding it everytime. This time i wrote it down. hehe",
    "173943113816902007/02/27 00:23:32mech6982If you're aiming for flight paths, you may as well just start your trip from the wetlands.  Pick up the Auberdine and Astranaar flighpaths on your way to the Barrens.  Once you're there you can grab Ratchet, take the boat to Booty Bay and nab it too.",
    "1739690306902006/09/19 06:11:32NirunSoloed at level 20, gnome warlock.\
\
I did not have any helpful flightpaths yet so this is how I did it.\
\
Flew to Westfall, then swam from there to Booty Bay. Just kept good distance to the shore and no one disturbed me.\
Took the FP in BB and then went on the boat from there to Ratchet and ran to Takar the Seer (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=6244) from there.\
\
After this, first instinct would be to run north, but instead I took my HS back to IF and ran to Westfall and grabbed my FP there and then hopped on the boat to Darkshore got the FP and ran from there to the tree.\
\
Finished my bussiness there, killed about 4 of them, then continued to Astranaar and took the FP there.\
\
This route was pretty fast and easy, and got me 4 new flight paths.",
    "173914106231716822007/08/20 09:12:01ChickibidiShe can't seduce the void either way - she can only seduce humans. \
\
Besides, when you can get something at 20, I like when you can actually GET IT at 20, with out help.",
    "1739171610111456892007/10/19 06:42:25lilacmooni agree, this was ridiculously easy, i think to make up for the excessively long trek to find the guy in the barrens, did it lvl 20 np :)",
    "1739177275201772752007/10/31 11:43:40madmanozzyUsing my 20th Level Human Warlock, This is how I completed this quest:\
\
Earlier in the game, get the Menethil Harbor flight path, then take the boat to Auberdine.  Get the flight path from there and proceed on foot to Astranaar and get the flight path and Hearthstone there as well as you'll need it to get back. \
\
Next, go from there south and follow the road east towards Raynewood retreat and continue past it until you come to a road on the right, which takes you south into the barrens. The Road is between Raynewood and the Splintertree outpost...just so you know, there is a Horde outpost at the entrance to the barrens, but     if you bare left, you'll find a hole in the outpost wall you can traverse and avoid the guards altogether. \
\
Travel onward into the barrens via the gold road...a 2nd outpost at the crossroads is here so go around. You'll reach your goal in no time. \
\
Once you get the quest to obtain the Heartswood, use your Hearthstone and go back to Astranaar...go to the ruins of Ordil'Aran and approach from the south. I only had to take out 2 Dark Strands and moved along the edge of the mountain to get the Heartswood as you don't have to be right upon it to interact with the tree. It helps to do it that way so you avoid causing other Dark Strands from attacking you.  \
\
Now, reverse your way back to Stormwind, visit Gakin, beat down the succubus...visit Gakin again. Enjoy your succubus..\
\
This is the way I did it, and was nearly hastle-free. I sicked my Voidwalker on the succubus and just sat back and watched the fight.",
