    "19206659811620352007/04/13 11:48:22IcemeltWe could only wish. You are attacked as soon as they spawn.",
    "1920144144401441442007/08/26 02:07:35jiyoungleThis comment may seem redundant, but I just wanted to clear up and verify the information from previous comments.  I just followed these steps today (Aug 26, 2007).  When I read all of the comments here, I got a little confused.  Hopefully this will help.  If not, feel free to rate it down.\
\
Basically, as soon as you take the quest, grab one of the lunchbox-looking things (Chest of Containment Coffers) and one of the scrolls (Cantation of Manifestation) from the table next to Jennea Cannon.  \
\
Head to the Blue Recluse (approximately at 38,84).  If you're entering the Mage Quarter from the Trade District and you take the southern path inside the quarter after the tunnel, it should be the first building on your left.  But, you'll probably be heading there from the Mage's Tower, so as soon as you get outside, jump off the right side and you should see the building.  \
\
Then, follow the advice of adders666 (six posts above this one).  I followed his instructions and it worked perfectly.  To reiterate, summon the first one in the basement, then go up the stairs and summon from within the fireplace, then go into the main room and go under one of the staircases to summon.  For each summon, once you've stunned the creature, use the Chest of Containment Coffers.  This will throw a coffer onto the ground and the creature will become trapped in it.  Pick up the coffer once it's filled.  Do this for each creature.  Once you have three of them, head back to Jennea.",
    "1920140149211400362007/08/18 14:56:49icaretakerThose items are on the table behind the quest giver.",
    "1920134108301341082007/08/08 01:54:17GrandPoobahThis reminds me so much of Ghostbusters. After you stun them you throw down the trap to dispose of them. A job well done!!",
    "1920134546101345462007/08/08 18:43:03AliariaI did this quest after much MUCH frustration because I kept dying from these little wankers.  But on my last one that I needed I was like \"Ok, I'm going to use the cantation in the kitchen\" so I did, and only got TWO of the mini-voidwalker looking things.  SO that is MUCH better than getting the snot beat out of you by three.",
    "19205294420529442007/03/18 00:30:54EmeraeldI went to the basement, and just 1 summoned, which was easy to kill and contain.  Then I went to the main floor and summoned and 3 showed up, promptly kicking my butt.  I rezzed and came back, went to the basement and summoned 1 again - no problem, got it.  Then I went up on the top floor and tried summoning.  Three showed up again!  So, I ran and at least didn't die.  Then I got the brilliant idea to log out and log back in.  Went to the basement and just 1 summoned. \
\
So, I think you can go to the basement, get 1, log out and back in, and go to the basement and get 1 again.  Much easier to handle as a mage than having 3 on you at once.",
    "19206215211620352007/04/04 17:46:37jmannThis quest seems to have changed since I last played an alliance mage (2 years ago).\
\
Back then, I'm certain the three Rift Spawns didn't attack as soon as they appeared.  You could easily deal with them one at a time before.",
    "19206333110633312007/04/07 11:57:28JimbodawgI went to the basement at level 15, killed it, contained it.\
Then went to that room, with the fireplace right above the basement, not the main floor, and found only one there. Then I went to the main floor and found one there. I did this quest easy at level 15, had no trouble whatsoever. Also, it's best to do this with someone else. The Rifts are annoying. :D",
    "19207109420710942007/04/22 15:12:57jestyrspawn and kill one in the basement.\
\
spawn and kill one upstairs, i went all the way into the farthest corner from the stairs just to make sure i didn't spawn any additional Rifts.\
\
for the third Rift i went into the kitchen (with the fireplace and Connor Rivers Apprentice Chef in it). i used the Cantation next to the fireplace to spawn the Rift, and only one came out. \
\
lvl 16 when i did it. do not use the Cantation in the main area as you will get rushed by 3 Rifts.",
    "192016356016352006/10/08 19:06:08PrailThere is one creature on each floor.",
    "19201789010178902006/12/24 07:54:05dirtmcgirtHow does one \"Stun\" the mana rifts?  I am getting mauled by several of these things at a time.",
    "19209228110922812007/05/28 07:10:23nemezis14563where is this blue recluse.I know it`s in mage sector but  where exactly ?",
    "19207288611620352007/04/25 17:22:16NaenthosThis is correct. I just did this quest with my second mage and reported the change. The Rift Spawns used to be non-agressive until attacked (if I recall correctly).",
    "19206203510620352007/04/04 13:56:18IcemeltA quest ment to kill you, as Blizzard does best. If you do this quest at 15 and try to kill all 3, you will die. If you don't have greens to buff up your toon, 2 will kill you too. If you die on this one you have to spawn outside Stormwind, total time waster.\
\
This is how to do the quest the easy way - one log out.\
\
Go to the basement and kill the 1st\
Go up to the kitchen next to the cook to spawn the 2nd\
Log out! Log In! (or die if you would  rather try it)\
Go back to the kitchen for the 3rd\
\
I was told that you could leave the completed Coffers on the floor in the basement and kitchen and only get one in the main room. I did this, still got two, went to the basement and my 1st coffer was gone.",
    "19205952530595252007/03/30 04:46:04EiviThe Chest of Containment Coffers and Cantation of Manifestation are on the table behind Jennea.  Make sure to pick them up before heading off the the Blue Recluse.",
    "19206659911633312007/04/13 11:50:10IcemeltWould be nice to know the exact location you spawned the 3rd rift. I experimented with several areas in the main room after containing the first two as we stated above.\
