    "1920148143201481432007/09/02 13:47:05depthchargeTried this quest a few times just summoning in the main room, quickly learned that was a mistake. So, I went down to the basement, summoned in the far back of the room, killed and contained with no problem. Went to kitchen stairs, summoned at the top of the stairs so as to not accidently  spawn any in the main room (made that mistake too, summoning in the middle of the room), killed and contained again no problem. Went to the top floor, summoned near the back wall, killed again and contained. Once you figure out where to spawn like I did, this quest is actually pretty easy. Did at Level 16 with minimal effort after planning my summons better.",
    "1920171353201713532007/10/18 20:11:18TebasileIf you are having trouble, follow the instructions given by [b]jiyongle[/b],  2 comments above this one... but in addition:\
\
Once inside the Blue Recluse, do the following to make things a little easier (I did this solo on a level 15 mage with the few quest greens I had received).\
[ol]\
[li]Go to the very bottom basement level [/li]\
[li]Move to the wall farthest from the stairs so anything you aggro from above won't make it to the stairs [/li]\
[li]Use your scroll [/li]\
[li]Kill the rift with a combination of your favorite damage spell and Frost Nova [/li]\
[li]Use the coffer on the stunned rift [/li]\
[li]Pick up the filled coffer[/li]\
[li][b]Now, rather than heading back upstairs, use your scroll again right there[/b] [/li]\
[li]Rinse and repeat until you have your other two[/li]\
[li]Hang out for 2-3 minutes after your last rift, and the upstairs will despawn so you can exit safely.\
[/ol]\
\
I found this quicker than moving around the place.",
