  ["Clearing the Way20"] = {
    "976112018npcVindicator Corin17986npcVindicator Corin179861950Exodar35019753297563976049761",
    "9761144852101448522007/08/27 13:00:44pudgenudgeSoloed this quest (Yeah for the XP buff)\
\
There are plenty of individual agents & Sabotures walking amongst the area.  Picking off these just takes patience and making your attacks from higher ground... The mountain ridges make excelent cover to walk all the way to the top of the coil mountain.  Not to mention that if you can handle picking off a few here and there, going to complete another mission and coming back to take out the respawns you should find this a relatively easy solo at lvl 19 or 20.  \
\
Bare in mind that since ALL of the Blood Elves here are Elites, they are little b's to kill anyway, but, again... some time and patients and taking it on solo is not a big deal.",
    "9761170074101700742007/10/16 23:14:29GararSoloed this with an 18 warrior, but it certainly wasn't worth the effort.\
\
First: there's a rare stealthed assassin running around.  Make sure she dies before you attempt soloing others.  The assassin is not elite, only silver.\
\
Second: just because it looks like there's only one mob there from one angle doesn't mean that there's actually only one.  There are a couple points where they spawn in a straight line on the path most travelled, most notably the very first set as you start heading up the hill.\
\
Third: if you aren't a hybrid class, this is going to be rough.  Healing is a major perk if you're dealing with elites.  What I knew would be a trivial exercise in patience on my druid turned into a major, delicate task on my new warrior.\
\
As for my specific strategy: If you pass the first group of two elves over the hills on the left, you'll come to a saboteur.  These don't have ranged attacks.  Make sure you're all clear (see above note on assassin), pull it with a crossbow, then just go to work.  Keep battle and demoralizing shouts up, thunder clap, sunder armor, rend--anything you can do to balance out the elite advantage without slowing your attacks.  If you're soloing, heroic strike isn't the best use for your rage until near the end of the fight.  Use Gift of the Naaru before you're on death's doorstep.  It's not like you're going to be able to save it for next fight if you have no other healing skills.  Wait for Gift to come off cooldown, then look to the agent straight up the hill past where you pulled the saboteur.  Agents have bows, so you have to charge that one and hope that the patrol from further up the hill doesn't see you.  Once in melee range, the fight is exactly like the saboteur, just different skills that you can't do much about coming at you.",
    "97614006350400632007/02/21 17:03:18RonikinVector Coil is at 23,54\
And reason why this quest is elite and lv20 is because the Blood Elf mobs that you have to kill are elites and at lv19 they are not easy to solo with a shaman.  Two at a time is what you will be usually having to try and kill.",
    "9761200792102007922007/12/13 17:00:50lcarnegievery hard even for 2 people if you get 2 or more elites after you. Not worth the reward either.",
    "9761137642111190152007/08/14 06:48:37shyienNope, this quest is a Draenai only quest.",
    "9761211198102111982008/01/01 20:30:10NeokunDo this at the same time as the other Vector Coil quest.  The elite 20 you get for help is very handy.",
