    "73152532052532006/11/30 17:18:50Calista1045This can be a little tough, I would suggest at least a couple other people for help. The prospector walks all the way through the ruins pulling everything, including things that spawn if he passes. All of the creatures are at least level 18, you will be dealing with at least three at a time. Also he has very low life and can be killed easily, make sure he doesn't get hit too often. As hard as it is I would definatly do this quest, it leads to a series that gives great exp and rewards.",
    "7317609530760952007/05/01 13:15:22schintusHe's got a respawn time of 8-10mins approx.",
    "731129961201299612007/07/31 17:27:24SaladinMake sure you let the prospector walk first, or else the Golems will agro on you instead of him. He will not stop to help you like most Escort quests, but move along instead. It's vital that you let him go first. Also, he is healable, so his health shouldn't be a problem if you can heal or use a bandage on him.",
    "73172082072082006/12/06 09:33:47MAVCMage / Druid combo is the way that I did this one.  The mage went ahead and cleared mobs before the prospector aggroed them,   and I (druid) stayed on the prospector to heal.  I'd throw a small heal on the mage every once in a while.  Also buffed the prospector with MotW and thorns.  He aggroed twice but I quickly took them off of him.  Real easy to do.",
    "731152829401528292007/09/14 09:45:59ChairmanKagaThis quest can be soloed as long as you know what to expect and can be prepared for it.  I just pulled it off with a level 21 mage.  I wouldn't recommend trying to solo this before 20.  This quest is easily done with two people, but if you're stuck on your own, I hope this helps get you through it.\
\
First, note that Remtravel is indeed oblivious.  He will not attack unless he is personally aggroed first, otherwise he will keep walking the scripted route.  Mobs attacking you are not his concern.  Mobs you aggro yourself will be ignored as well.  If you let him lead, he will draw the initial aggro and stop.  This can be useful if you need a few seconds to catch your breath, but don't leave him alone too long -- he can't solo these mobs and he can't withstand too much punishment from them.  If more than one mob is on him, you need to intervene quickly.  AoE attacks are useful here, as he rarely accumulates much threat and any decent damage will get the mobs onto you instead.\
\
Second, avoid the use of snares (Frost Nova, Entangling Roots, etc).  If you snare and attempt to pull back for a more opportune attack, the mobs will drop threat on you and switch to something else in melee range -- Remtravel.\
\
Now to tell you what to expect, besides the golems infesting the whole place.\
\
When you begin the escort, there are a couple tents straight ahead and a ramp and scaffold along the right side.  Remtravel will eventually walk up that ramp.  This cues a single trogg to spawn.  This trogg always seems to ignore Remtravel and go for you, so be prepared to dispatch it quickly so Remtravel doesn't get too far ahead of you.\
\
Shortly after this, he will investigate Hollee's tent (he will comment \"Oh, that's Hollee's tent, and it's empty\")  Two troggs will spawn from the back right corner of the camp and go for Remtravel.\
\
Now he will start walking down into the more open area of the dig site.  At the far end, straight ahead, is another ramp and scaffold, with a small hill to the left.  Remember this spot.\
\
His path will take him down into the dig site, to the left and back around the other side of the wall to the dead end, then turn around and start heading back out to the start point.  On his way out, he will investigate that ramp and scaffold I mentioned earlier.  When he does, this will trigger two troggs to spawn on the hill to the left, one of them being a caster that likes Fireball.  The caster will drop Remtravel in two shots, so you need to draw its aggro [i]immediately[/i].  Personally I stood on the hill and cast Fire Blast on it while it was spawning.  Even so, it will get one Fireball off on Remtravel before switching to you (both troggs aggro Remtravel immediately upon spawning), so you also need to get the melee trogg off of him and then take them both down before they manage to kill you instead.\
\
If you get past this, you're pretty much clear, you just have to get him back to the front, past the few golems that have respawned, but those should be easy compared to what you just did.",
