    "2078123795101237952007/07/20 07:46:12PheliaThis is very easy as a shaman with this tactic.\
When you are getting close to the captain there is a log at the shore (see the screenshot). Before he turns hostile pop a Earthbind Totem close to the log.\
Then go close enough to get the mob to aggro, now use a Shock on him to keep him of your totems, Frost Shock is a great if you've got it to make kiting him abit easier.\
Then run back to the log and pop a Searing Totem. Then just run around the log (or back and forth to keep him on the opposite side) this will be fairly easy since he will be slowed.\
Make sure to put out new totems before they expire so he doesn't catch up with you.\
The Searing Totem will kill him fairly fast but if you have enough mana for it throw a few Shocks at him.",
    "20787465620746562007/04/28 23:20:29NepenthesSolo'd as a 21 firemage.    I had him evade and had to start the fight over, so I opened with pyroblast and just used blink/frost nova to keep him away from me.  Should be even easier as a frost mage, just kite him around.",
    "207810155231748452007/06/09 20:02:51xinaxdazexAs an alternative for druids, you can start off by chain rooting and casting star/moonfire to dot him up taking him down to half health or more. Once he's down that low, you can hop in to kittie form and whack away. You might want to save a potion, since he hits rather hard.\
\
Try to get the root off quickly since he'll hit you pretty hard when he first becomes aggressive.",
    "20788140850814082007/05/11 12:50:36KungFuOperaYou are left with Gyromast's Key after completing this quest.  As far as I can tell, there's no reason to hang on to it.  The Threshwackonator won't accept it again.",
    "20781942730194272007/01/05 04:39:26entropicdragonOn the other hand, he will follow you quite a ways if you don't head towards the captain. I got him all the way to Auberdine before he got bored and despawned (I don't know whether it's a timer or a distance-from-start meter that controls this.)",
    "20788140611752792007/05/11 12:48:55KungFuOperaSucceptible to Psychic Scream, so I imagine a warlock's Fear would work, too, making this encounter a piece of cake for that class.",
    "20781339240133922006/12/11 10:46:15costabileWyou have the Threshwakonator following you, and you get close to the captain, the robot will spontaneously turn aggressive and attack you. He is level 20 Elite, and hits pretty hard, so be ready.  If you need to escape or heal, run into the water, he won't follow very far.  Of course, if you do that, he'll go into evade/fast heal mode, so you can't just attack him from a distance without being hit.",
    "2078212252102122522008/01/03 13:56:28ZentralI f you aren't a alchemist or walrock uou should save the Elixir of Water breathing you get from this quest, you may need it later.",
    "2078146913101469132007/08/31 00:24:58drakaIt's possible to solo him as a 20 druid, a few scroll/food buffs and all green gear. The first time I soloed him as a 21-22 druid (I forget), I was able to stealth far enough away in cat form and root him from afar. This time, however, he followed very closely and saw through my stealth. I didn't have talented stealth, either. \
\
In any case, rejuv and root, then move away and regrowth, then melee in bear form. As I got down to less than 1/3 health, I bashed, rooted him again, heal/regrowth/rejuv again, and took him down with very little mana to spare. :-) I don't know if I'd melee him in cat form, however; he hits hard and potions are really last resort for me.",
