    "47409507010950702007/06/01 01:28:11marcusddsAs a rogue, pretty much not soloable while the quest is yellow. Was cake with a similar level warrior. Tip of the day: make sure you have something to counter runners - either direct damage ranged to finish them quick, DoTs, or slows. Otherwise any of them will probably bring friends when the invitation was only for one.",
    "4740193720101937202007/11/30 02:40:07wa12lockyes as above said kill some of them coastrunners appear coming from the water kill them and 2 more appear kill one or two and murk appears with a hunter there ya go murkdeep.",
    "47407094810709482007/04/22 09:24:08CybersonixSoloed as a lvl 18 druid. Very easy. Murkdeeps spawn when you kill 3 groups of murlocs in  36.76.  First there are hunters and warriors murlocs then 3 coastrunner on very low lvl then a small group of hunter or something. After that murkdeep spawn with one guard.",
    "4740137862101378622007/08/14 14:06:41Linaru[18 Rogue]\
\
I started clearing the area, but I must have aggroed the guard (a Warrior) because Murkdeep came after me. I killed the Warrior, then Gouged him so I could use a Wool Bandage. I used Sinister Strike and Eviscerate on him from there, and he died right when I got the \"Low Health\" message.\
\
So if you're lucky, you'll find Murkdeep already there, and I think he only had 1 guard. If you die, he'll probably just stay there, and it doesn't look like his guards respawn.",
    "47407435820743582007/04/28 10:31:19Icemelt[Shaman 15]\
\
For those of you that do not know, advice from hunters should only be tried by hunters (and maybe warlocks). For a very long time now, hunters have been known as the \"solo class\" because they really have two players: the hunter and a meat shield (pet).\
\
Note This!! - Any time a hunter says it can be done and you are not a hunter, it is a totaly different game.\
\
This said, I did complete the quest as a level 15 Shaman. Here's how..\
\
As said above, pulling the mobs in singles or smaller groups is correct. The problem is when facing Murkdeep. Several quests in the game will require you to kill a \"named\" NPC and he/she will almost always have \"bodyguards\". This one is no exception. A hunter above states \"easy to solo lvl 12hunter LOL kiting ftw :D\" and he's full of it. Post the video friend. I would bet he completed the quest in the same way or very similar to the other hunters, sending in pet on a few pulled mobs and letting his \"meat shield\" take the damage. Kiting is not easy and with the new daze mechanics, I would bet all my gold that he did not \"kite\" the mobs (probably doesen't know what kiting is).\
\
If you have any ranged abilities, start off with those on Murkdeep. I used Lightning after placing a Stoneclaw totem about half way in my cast range. Draenei have a racial HoT (heal over time) that I used after a nice big Nuke on the Murkdeep and I plop a Fire Nova and after plop a Flamtoung. At this point I was at a bit more than half health, my HoT was gone and the bodyguards were about to rush me. I self heal to fill my bar.\
\
Murkdeep is now at 1/4th health, but it's not over yet. I've not done any damage to the guards, so new totems would be toast and Claw tot is on cooldown. I don't have much mana, so I Flame shock, recharge my shield and plop a Stoneskin. The entire time I'm backing up to make distance between me and the guards, I had to be careful not to evade the mobs (another reason kiting is hard here), but being on the brink of evading mobs can be a good thing. A final Earth Shock kills Murkdeep, I now have only 14% health and the guards are wicked pissed. I drop my Earthbind and turn-tail, running further away from the mobs origional spawn point. Sure enough, they evade.\
\
I run up to the corpse of Murkdeep, grab my loot and eat/drink atop his fallen body. Success!\
\
Good Luck and Death to Murkdeep!",
    "474034395034392006/11/11 10:02:11madroxeMurkdeep can be found at 36, 76 (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=10323) on the shore, surrounded by Murloc hunters, warriors, and coastrunners in a small camp.",
    "4740161186101611862007/10/01 05:27:09BlueDog[18 Priest]\
\
- Cleared the area around the buildings without walking near the bonfire.\
- Walked near bonfire and 3 coastrunners (lvl 13) spawned running in from the water, killed them.\
 2 warriors (lvl 15 I think, can't remember) spawned. I managed to pull only one and when he died Murkdeep + another warrior spawned. Killed Murkdeep and ran away :)",
    "47401310461134392007/08/02 11:45:40KedanaIt seems this quest is slightly bugged.. If you clear the camp and nothing seems to happen, check the water nearby for a stray murloc swimming around.  \
\
I cleared the camp 3 times in a row of the hunters & warriors, and nothing else spawned or ran up from the water.  I had decided to leave and was running north along the coast when I happened to run into a lone Coastrunner swimming around in the sea about 60 yards north of the camp.  When i killed him, the 2 warriors immediately ran up from the sea, and once I killed them, Murkdeep appeared.",
