    "2499106899201068992007/06/19 05:35:19JebekkuSoloed at lvl 9 night elf druid. just pull the other two ones outside kill them then pull the Oakenscowl then just jump back and do the entaglig roots and when its going to break do it again easy? :)",
    "2499176674101766742007/10/30 03:34:03TurboXL10 Night Elf Rogue - solo'd\
\
This was easier than it first appeared when looking at the situation. Just clean out the field in front of the cave. This leaves you with 3 mobs: Oaky, his \"bodyguard\", and the cave entrance wanderer.\
\
Pull the wanderer once he's at his furthest point out, no issue here. For my attempt at this quest (and judging from most other posts on here as well) Oaky's \"bodyguard\" isn't linked to him in any way, just pull him as usual with your bow, throwing weapon, Starfire, Smite, etc.\
\
Now, for Oaky himself, he sure didn't seem like an elite, although he was a level below me. Being a Rouge, stealth behind him... get a Backstab off, wait a few moments go gather Energy back, then hit a Gouge, walk behind him and get off another Backstab. At this point, pop Evasion, get off 2 SS's before hitting the finishing move (either one would work, I believe I went with Eviscerate). He was down to about 35% health left, and my Evasion time was almost up. Gather Energy again, and start over from Gouge; he'll be just about dead after the ensuing Backstab/SS.\
\
No potions or bandages needed, just a little planning for your first \"group\" quest.",
