EDIT2: Did other path thats pretty safe with warlock. You can do this quest without dieing (even on PVP realm). I went over stonetalon mountains. (Darkshore=>Ashenwale=>Stonetalon M.=>Barrens)",
    "17161171101172006/09/12 20:51:07sketchedIn the middle of the Barrens, you should come to a fork in  the road with Camp Taurajo to the west of you.  There looks to be a small wooden tee-pee looking camp directly east of you.  Go past that & through the dinosaurs.  There are 2 white tents in the distance. Talk to Takar the Seer",
    "1716167037101670372007/10/12 23:21:58campbellmom549So many people make this out to be harder than it is.  I took the boat to Theramore.  From there I ran to the Barrens.  I cannot emphasize enough sticking precisely to the roads.  I did aggro four mobs along the way.  But I made sure my armor was all repaired.  And I summoned my Voidwalker and put him on defensive.  When a mob aggrod, I took the first hit, and the voidwalker immediately taunted the aggro off.  I never stopped running.  After I got a little ways away (far enough that the mob couldn't catch up, but still close enough that my pet didn't de-spawn) I put myself on autorun and put the pet on passive.  He would then start running to catch up with me.  Eventually he outran the mob and it dropped off.  I never needed to stop and never did a single corpserun.",
    "1716147081201470812007/08/31 10:17:09Bdgamer710Its better to go through ashenvale from Darkshore because you need to go to ashenvale for the next quest and you will already have the flight point.",
    "1716104424101613752007/06/14 17:51:18jrodmanPersonally, at level 20 I would choose an alternate route:  From eastern kingdoms take the boat to darkshore, and then walk south into ashenvale, following the road east across ashenvale and then turn south following the signs into the barrens.  The entrance to the barrens from ashenvale is guarded by horde guards, but there is a gap in the fence to the left (east) that you can pass through without attracting their attention.\
\
This route is a little longer, but it should not require any corpserunning.  A matter of taste, perhaps.",
    "1716174346101743462007/10/24 15:38:34soulweaverthe easy route that i took was from the wetlands took the boat to darkshore but jump out when the other continant loads then swim to the south edge of darkshore and follow the road to ashenvale,go itno astranaar and get fp and set your hearth at the inn there, then go east out of astranaar on the road follow signs to barrens,once you are in the barrens start to climb on top of the hills there and continue south it will be a little more than half way down the map on the right hand side,or 49,57 for those with co ord. the hills you are on will allow you to take a downward slope to this area.you will avoid mobs and horde this way.after turning in the quest hearth to astranaar and there you go half the walk time. then just remeber to set your hearth back to were you want it =)",
