    "171671943121613752007/04/24 01:54:14unitepunxDont know why you're marked down. The best way to get to The Barrens from SW is to get to Menethil Harbor in the Wetlands first. Very useful to get the Flight Path here anyways of you want to get over to Kalimdor for Darnassus and Exodar. Take the boat to Theramore Isle in Duskwallow Marsh. You'll have to go though Duskwallow Marsh, so use your spare armor, cause you will most likely die a few times. The enterance to the Barrens is directly west of Theramore Isle, but you'll need to go up and around. Just follow the path. Once in the Barrens you'll need to keep an eye on the path, or go on the path, north and then west when it splits a little ways up. Camp Taurajo should be visible from there.",
    "17167606240760622007/05/01 12:01:11trena792001I take the longer route but you are less likely to die........If from wetlands you go to Auberdine (remember to get the flight path.  Then head south and follow rd to Ashenvale and Astranaar (again get flight path) then head south(east) and when the road branches go right which continues south when you come to the barrens (very obvious the scenary turns brown go left there is an unmanned little sneak entrance there then folow the path down (avoiding towns!) also if you think about it you may want to remember to go to Ratchet on your way down and grap that flight path as this is useful later and will save you the walking!",
    "1716139684301396842007/08/17 17:58:56aisthesisThis is what worked for me:  Go to Westfall, head out to the coast near the Lighthouse (to the southwest) and swim to Booty Bay using your Unending Breath.  The coords. for Booty Bay are 26.75.  Stay away from the coast so you don't aggro any of the land creatures (they are fast and will swim out to attack you).  There weren't any aggro sea creatures that I could see.  Once at Booty Bay, get the FP, take the ship to Ratchet, get the FP there, and take the road out of Ratchet west, but avoid getting too close to Crossroads (you can cut across to the road heading south).  Then, head south on the road to coord. 49.57.  At level 20, I stayed away from any buildings I could see from the road, and didn't run into any guards.  When you get close to the coords you should be able to see the tent Takar is in front of.  Then, you can reverse back to Ratchet or hearth out.",
    "1716180370111396842007/11/07 04:43:10lupokibaSorry, but I tried this route. I wasn't able to find Booty Bay. At the coord you gave in Westfall there is only an old cracked ship. Nothing else.\
