    "600113284921348802007/08/05 23:20:03AntubisActually, I think that no matter what you can still complete the quest.  When I summoned her, a hunter outside killed her before I could, but I was still able to talk to the spirit and complete the quest.",
    "6001133690101336902007/08/07 08:21:34blaze93This quest can be made easier if you have Alchemy as one of your skills. That way you can provide your own potions to buff yourself more. I personally used a Weak Troll's Blood Potion and an Elixer of Minor Defense. They help a lot.",
    "6001142560101425602007/08/22 23:49:41JingoistThe easiest way to kill the moonkins (both outside the cave and Lunaclaw) himself is to root, moonfire, and then wait. Let your mana regen a bit, then when roots break, re-root and re-moonfire. Back up, repeat as necessary. Just avoid spamming wrath, because it runs you OOM quickly and it gives a chance for the roots to break early.",
    "6001211392102113922008/01/02 05:36:02DairuinIt's possible to solo the quest without having to die in the cave to get in, just avoid the moonkins outside and get up on the rocks above the entrance. Then you can drop down without aggroing the guard (who will have his back to you), enter the cave, kill Lunaclaw and HS back out.",
    "60017124340712432007/04/22 20:14:05asdfg195I had a real hard time killing the level 13 moonkin infront of the cave.  After failing multiple times, I decided to rank 1 moonfire kite him to the guards in auderdine.",
    "60013488090348802007/02/12 19:29:21ajheydeIf you play on a crowded server, it may be a good idea to look around before using the dust.  If there is another player nearby, he/she might kill Lunaclaw before you.  If that happens, you must abandon the quest and get it again from Mathrengyl Bearwalker to get the dust back.",
    "6001151319401513192007/09/10 14:59:39ThodtIf you did Zenn's Bidding ( http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=488 ) you should have a 5-stack of Severed Voodoo Claws in your inventory ( http://www.wowhead.com/?item=5457 ). These reduce melee damage from mobs by a small amount but are great for this quest. Just debuff Lunaclaw and you should have no issues whatsoever.",
